 Go to Dashboard, Appearance, menus and create a new menu called Menu Korean

 Click Create Menu. 

 Then in Menu structure, Menu Settings, click it to be Primary 한국어

 This will make it primary menu for when we're in Korean

 Then add the links via Custom Links dropdown menu. 

URL: #intro
Link Text: 꿀맛을 소개합니다

 URL: #food
 Link Text: 메뉴

 URL: #locations
 Link Text: 오시는길

To get the various other elements translated, you can go to Dashboard, Languages, Strings translations and put in the Korean versions of all those phrases 